the other himalayan river, the brahmaputra flows through the northeast, mostly through assam. south of punjab lies the aravalli range which cuts rajasthan into two. the western half of rajasthan is occupied by the thar desert. the vindhyas cut across central india, particularly through madhya pradesh and signify the start of the deccan plateau, which covers almost the whole of the southern peninsula. the deccan plateau is bounded by the sahyadri (western ghats) range to the west and the eastern ghats to the east. the plateau is more arid than the plains, as the rivers that feed the area, such 